race.comment: NIGHTCAPPED (11) was quickly back on track second-up when finding one better over 1350m at Ipswich. Hit the line well and will strip fitter. She is capable of sitting closer and won't have to improve much to give this a shake. Stablemate SUNLORD (2) resumes and the well-performed galloper will come into his own over a bit further. The 1400m is a good starting point and Ben Thompson sticks from a recent Deagon trial. It won't surprise to see him feature. THE TORQUE FACTOR (9) resumes for the Kendrick yard and is right up to this if presented forward. The 349 days away is a niggle, but he was sharp on the inner track here in the latest of his two trials. The well-bred galloper races forward and has plenty of scope for improvement. MAPLE DOOR (6) found a 70 at Eagle Farm a stretch last time, but he improved winning a CL4 here prior over this distance. Has a low gate and has to be kept onside.
